.TH WEH 1 "2026" "weh 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
weh \- tiny C image viewer for X11 and Wayland
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B weh
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
[\fIIMAGE\fR...|\fIDIRECTORY\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B weh
is a minimal image viewer whose only job is to display an image. It runs
natively on both X11 and Wayland (via SDL3) and supports a broad range of
formats:
.IP \[bu] 2
Static raster formats supported by GEGL (PNG, JPEG, TIFF, BMP, PSD,
single-frame WebP and AVIF, PNM, HDR, EXR, TGA, etc.).
.IP \[bu]
Animated formats supported by gdk-pixbuf (GIF, APNG, animated WebP,
animated AVIF if the loader is installed, MNG).
.IP \[bu]
SVG, rasterized on demand at the exact target pixel size so it stays
crisp at any zoom level.
.PP
Arguments are optional. With no argument,
.B weh
opens a blank window; drag-drop an image, multiple images, or a
directory onto it to start viewing.

If a
.I DIRECTORY
is given, all openable images in it are listed (sorted case-insensitively
by basename) and
.BR , " / " .
navigate the list with wrap-around.

If multiple
.I IMAGE
arguments are given (or a multi-file drag-drop occurs), the given files
form an ad-hoc playlist in the order they were supplied; navigation
keys move through that list. No directory scan is performed — only the
files explicitly listed appear in the playlist.

If a single
.I IMAGE
is given, no playlist is built and the navigation keys are no-ops until
a directory or multi-file drop arrives.
.PP
The image is fitted inside the window with the original aspect ratio
preserved. When the window's aspect does not match the image's, the
non-image area is filled with a configurable background color (default
white). On compositors that honor it, the window itself is locked to the
image's aspect ratio.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Show version information and exit.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-fullscreen
Start in fullscreen mode. Equivalent to pressing
.B f
once the window is open.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-nearest
Start with nearest-neighbor texture sampling (pixel-art mode). Equivalent
to pressing
.B n
once the window is open.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-aspect\-lock
Do not request aspect-ratio locking from the compositor. May be toggled
at runtime with
.BR a .
.TP
.B \-\-x11
Force SDL to use the X11 video backend. On a Wayland session this routes
through XWayland. Useful when the Wayland backend misbehaves with a
particular compositor.
.TP
.B \-\-wayland
Force SDL to use the Wayland video backend (no XWayland fallback).
.TP
.BR \-z ", " \-\-zoom = \fIN\fR
Initial zoom factor. 1.0 means the image is fitted to the window;
2.0 zooms in 2x, 0.5 zooms out by half. Default 1.0.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-title = \fISTR\fR
Override the window title. By default the title is the image filename.
.TP
.BI \-\-app-id = STR
Override the application identifier used as the Wayland \fIxdg-shell\fR
app_id and as the X11 \fIWM_CLASS\fR. This is the string a compositor
matches against a
.B .desktop
file to look up the application icon. Default
.B io.github.notmugi.weh .
.TP
.BI \-\-bg = #RRGGBB
Background and letterbox color, in hex. Default
.B #ffffff
(white).
.SH CONTROLS
.TP
.B f
Toggle fullscreen.
.TP
.B r
Hard reset: zoom to 1.0, recenter on the image, clear flips and rotation.
The image is refit into the current window; the window itself is not
resized or moved. Tile mode and aspect lock are preserved; pause/skim
state is preserved.
.TP
.B i
Toggle the info overlay (bottom-left). Shows the full path, file size,
pixel dimensions, format, animation flag with frame count and current
frame, current zoom level, and the directory position if applicable.
.TP
.B b
Toggle the keybind cheat-sheet, a centered list of every key and what
it does. Useful for first-time use.
.TP
.B n
Toggle nearest-neighbor texture sampling. Useful for pixel art; default
is bilinear.
.TP
.B a
Toggle the WM-aspect-lock at runtime. Initial state is set by
.B \-\-no\-aspect\-lock .
.TP
.B h
Flip horizontal (toggle).
.TP
.B v
Flip vertical (toggle).
.TP
.B k
Rotate 90 degrees counterclockwise.
.TP
.B l
Rotate 90 degrees clockwise.
.TP
.B t
Toggle tile mode. While on, the image repeats outward from the center,
forming a grid. The number keys
.BR 1 \- 9
choose the tile radius (number of tiles to each side of the center),
producing a (2N+1)x(2N+1) grid. Default radius is 1 (3x3 grid).
.TP
.B w
Toggle mirrored tiling (only meaningful in tile mode). When on,
alternating tiles are flipped so seams match perfectly.
.TP
.BR 1 \- 9
In tile mode, sets the tile radius from 1 (3x3) to 9 (19x19).
.TP
.B p
Pause or resume animation playback (animated images only). On the first
press, the full animation is decoded into RAM so that arbitrary-frame
skim is instant.
.TP
.B \-
Step to the previous animation frame (animated images only). Implicitly
pauses playback. Wraps from frame 0 to the last frame.
.TP
.B =
Step to the next animation frame (animated images only). Implicitly
pauses playback. Wraps from the last frame back to frame 0.
.TP
.BR , " / " .
Previous / next image in the directory list, with wrap-around. Only
available when launched with a directory argument or after a directory
is drag-dropped.
.TP
.B Home / End
Jump to the first / last image in the directory list.
.TP
.BR q ", " Esc
Quit.
.TP
Mouse wheel
Zoom in/out around the currently centered point.
.TP
Left-drag
Pan. The image tracks the cursor 1:1.
.TP
Drop a file or directory
Open the dropped path in place. Drag-and-drop works on the blank window
too.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Window closed cleanly.
.TP
.B 1
The image or directory failed to load.
.TP
.B 2
Invalid command-line usage.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $PREFIX/bin/weh
The executable.
.TP
.I $PREFIX/share/applications/weh.desktop
The desktop entry used by Wayland compositors to discover the icon
via the application's
.B app_id .
.TP
.I $PREFIX/share/icons/hicolor/scalable/apps/weh.svg
.TQ
.I $PREFIX/share/icons/hicolor/SIZExSIZE/apps/weh.png
Application icons under the
.B hicolor
theme.
.SH NOTES ON ICONS
On Wayland there is no protocol mechanism for a client to push its own
icon. Compositors match the window's
.I app_id
against a
.B .desktop
file installed under
.B $XDG_DATA_DIRS/applications
and read the icon from it. The
.B make install
target installs both
.B weh.desktop
and the icon files into the system locations expected by freedesktop. On
X11,
.B weh
additionally pushes the icon directly via
.BR SDL_SetWindowIcon ,
so the icon works without an installed
.B .desktop
file.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR feh (1),
.BR sxiv (1),
.BR imv (1)
